100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On September 24, 1925, the world witnessed significant developments as the League of Nations convened in Geneva, discussing the ongoing tensions in the Middle East. In the United States, a new wave of labor strikes erupted, signaling rising discontent among workers seeking better conditions. Meanwhile, in France, preparations for the upcoming Paris Exposition intensified, promising a showcase of modern art and industry.
